folder: Jamaica Avenue & Hempstead Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Jamaica Ave., south side, at its intersection with Hempstead Ave., showing in a set of two views the Thomas Callister wagon shop.  It was operated by Callister Bros Inc. in 1925 as an automobile shop. From 1860 to 1873 by Thomas Callister as a carriage and wagon factory.

May 1923.
View 2: April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

folder: Jamaica Avenue & Hempstead Avenue, Queens, NY
text:
Jamaica Avenue, near the S.E. corner of Hempstead Avenue, showing the house of Mrs. Higbie in 1860. It was owned in 1873 by Lewis Rose and in 1891 by Elizabeth Rose. The rear of the house faces on Jamaica Avenue, whereas the front is turned toward Hempstead Avenue.

Views 1, 2:Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

View 1:May, 1923
View 2:April, 1925

View 3: P.L.Sperr
